[% META
   title = "Database Schema Management - Result Classes Approach"
   description = "Comprehensive guide to managing Comserv database schema using DBIx::Class Result classes and DBSchemaManager. Learn how to create, update, and maintain database tables through code-first approach."
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "database,schema-management"
   page_version = "0.01"
   last_updated = "Thu Dec 25 2025"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/Schema.tt,v 0.01 2025/12/25 shanta Exp - Database schema management using Result classes (NOT SQL files)' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Database Schema Management</h1>
    <h2 style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Using DBIx::Class Result Classes (Code-First Approach)</h2>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-12-25 | 
        Version: 0.01 |
        Status: Code-First Schema Management |
        Target Audience: Developers, Database Administrators
    </div>

    <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
    <div id="toc" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-large) 0;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">Table of Contents</h3>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><a href="#overview">1. Overview</a></li>
            <li><a href="#architecture">2. Architecture</a></li>
            <li><a href="#result-classes">3. Result Classes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#creating-tables">4. Creating Tables from Result Classes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#modifying-schema">5. Modifying Schema</a></li>
            <li><a href="#best-practices">6. Best Practices</a></li>
            <li><a href="#troubleshooting">7. Troubleshooting</a></li>
            <li><a href="#related-docs">8. Related Documentation</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- OVERVIEW SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Overview</h2>
            
            <div style="background: var(--info-color, #d1ecf1); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-border, #17a2b8); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 0;"><strong>🔑 Key Principle:</strong> Comserv uses a <strong>code-first schema management approach</strong>. Database tables are defined as <strong>DBIx::Class Result classes</strong> in your source code, NOT as SQL files.</p>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Why Result Classes, Not SQL Files?</h3>
            <table style="width: 100%; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <thead>
                    <tr style="background: var(--secondary-color, #0066cc); color: white;">
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Aspect</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Result Classes ✅</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">SQL Files ❌</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong>Version Control</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Tracked in Git with full change history</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Difficult to track incremental changes</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong>Relationships</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Defined in code with helper methods</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Only foreign keys, no ORM integration</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong>Type Safety</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Perl Moose types enforce constraints</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">No compile-time type checking</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong>Code Integration</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Native to Catalyst, full ORM support</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Requires manual schema-to-code sync</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ARCHITECTURE SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="architecture" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Architecture</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">File Organization</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Comserv/
├── lib/Comserv/
│   ├── Model/
│   │   ├── DBSchemaManager.pm          ← Schema management engine
│   │   └── Schema/
│   │       └── Ency/
│   │           └── Result/             ← Result class definitions
│   │               ├── Todo.pm
│   │               ├── User.pm
│   │               ├── DocumentationMetadataIndex.pm
│   │               └── ... (60+ Result classes)
│   └── Util/
│       └── DBSchemaManager.pm          ← Helper utilities
└── sql/
    ├── 20251216_ai_chat_feature_phase1_tables.sql (archived reference only)
    └── ... (historical SQL files - reference only, not used for creation)</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">How It Works at Application Startup</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>1. Application starts (script/comserv_server.pl)
   ↓
2. Catalyst loads all Result classes from lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/
   ↓
3. DBSchemaManager.initialize_schema() called
   ↓
4. For each Result class:
   - Check if table exists
   - If not: Create table from Result class definition
   - If exists: Compare schema vs Result definition (optional upgrade)
   ↓
5. Application ready to serve requests
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RESULT CLASSES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="result-classes" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Result Classes</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Anatomy of a Result Class</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>package Comserv::Model::Schema::Ency::Result::DocumentationMetadataIndex;

use Moose;
use MooseX::Types::Moose qw(Str Int);
use DateTime;

__PACKAGE__->table('documentation_metadata_index');
__PACKAGE__->add_columns(
    id => {
        data_type => 'integer',
        is_auto_increment => 1,
        is_nullable => 0,
    },
    file_path => {
        data_type => 'varchar',
        size => 512,
        is_nullable => 0,
    },
    title => {
        data_type => 'varchar',
        size => 512,
    },
    searchable_text => {
        data_type => 'longtext',
    },
    indexed_at => {
        data_type => 'datetime',
        set_on_create => 1,
    },
);

__PACKAGE__->set_primary_key('id');
__PACKAGE__->add_unique_constraint(['file_path']);

1;</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Components</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Package Declaration</strong>: Follows pattern <code>Comserv::Model::Schema::{DatabaseName}::Result::{TableName}</code></li>
                <li><strong>__PACKAGE__->table()</strong>: Maps Perl class to database table name</li>
                <li><strong>add_columns()</strong>: Defines all table columns with types and constraints</li>
                <li><strong>set_primary_key()</strong>: Designates the primary key column</li>
                <li><strong>add_unique_constraint()</strong>: Adds unique indexes on specified columns</li>
                <li><strong>Relationships</strong>: Define foreign keys and ORM relationships (optional)</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CREATING TABLES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="creating-tables" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Creating Tables from Result Classes</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 1: Create the Result Class</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Write your Result class in <code>lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/YourTableName.pm</code></p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 2: Start Application</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Development
perl script/comserv_server.pl

# Production
starman -p 5000 script/comserv_server.psgi</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 3: Verify Table Creation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Check application logs or use admin interface:</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Via admin interface
/admin/database_schema

# Via MySQL CLI
USE ency;
SHOW TABLES LIKE 'your_table_name';
DESCRIBE your_table_name;</code></pre>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MODIFYING SCHEMA SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="modifying-schema" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. Modifying Schema</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Adding a Column</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Edit the Result class file, add to <code>add_columns()</code>:</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>new_field => {
    data_type => 'varchar',
    size => 255,
    is_nullable => 1,
    default_value => 'some_value',
},</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Save file, restart application. DBSchemaManager detects the difference and creates the column.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Renaming a Column</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">ℹ️ <strong>Note:</strong> Direct column renames require careful migration. Consider:</p>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Create new column with correct name</li>
                <li>Copy data from old column</li>
                <li>Test thoroughly</li>
                <li>Remove old column in next release</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Adding an Index</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Use <code>add_index()</code> in Result class:</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>__PACKAGE__->add_index(['file_path', 'user_id']);</code></pre>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BEST PRACTICES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="best-practices" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6. Best Practices</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ DO</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Define all schema changes in Result classes</strong> - Keep Result classes as single source of truth</li>
                <li><strong>Use meaningful table and column names</strong> - Follow snake_case for database, CamelCase for classes</li>
                <li><strong>Add comments in Result classes</strong> - Document complex column definitions</li>
                <li><strong>Create indexed relationships</strong> - Ensure foreign key columns are indexed</li>
                <li><strong>Test schema changes in development first</strong> - Always test before production deployment</li>
                <li><strong>Track Result classes in Git</strong> - Version control is your audit trail</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">❌ DON'T</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Manually edit database tables</strong> - Always update Result class first</li>
                <li><strong>Create SQL files for schema creation</strong> - Use Result classes instead</li>
                <li><strong>Import raw SQL dumps</strong> - Use Result class definitions + data-only backups</li>
                <li><strong>Leave Result classes out of sync with database</strong> - Run comparison checks regularly</li>
                <li><strong>Forget to test relationships</strong> - Many bugs come from incorrect foreign key definitions</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="troubleshooting" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7. Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-table-not-created" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">Table Not Created After Restart</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Cause:</strong> Result class not properly loaded by Catalyst</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Check file is in correct directory: <code>lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/</code></li>
                    <li>Verify package name matches file name</li>
                    <li>Check application logs for errors</li>
                    <li>Run <code>perl -c lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/YourClass.pm</code> to check syntax</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-column-mismatch" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">Schema Mismatch After Code Change</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Cause:</strong> Database hasn't been updated to match Result class changes</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Use admin interface: <code>/admin/compare_schema</code></li>
                    <li>Review differences</li>
                    <li>Use <code>/admin/migrate_schema</code> to apply changes</li>
                    <li>Test application functionality thoroughly</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RELATED DOCUMENTATION SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="related-docs" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8. Related Documentation</h2>
            
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
